cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.CC, cs.DS

Reasoning: The paper deals with equational properties of models of guarded (co-)recursion, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) since the paper formulates axioms for guarded fixpoint operators and studies their equational properties. The second likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages) since the paper deals with models of guarded recursion and introduces the notion of guarded trace operator on a category. The third likely category is cs.TL (Topology and Category Theory) since the paper discusses models of guarded recursion such as complete metric spaces or the topos of trees. The fourth likely category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity) since the paper mentions the satisfaction of all Conway axioms by a unique dagger operation. The fifth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the paper deals with recursion and fixpoint operators.
